---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import HubCard from '../../../components/HubCard.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
    title="Performance and CSS"
    description="Performance-focused CSS architecture guidance."
>
    <section class="site-hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Performance</p>
        <p class="summary-badge">Summary Page</p>

        <h1>
            Performance-first CSS
        </h1>

        <p class="intro">
            CSS architecture affects maintainability, rendering behaviour, and
            long-term performance.
        </p>

        <p class="summary-note">
            This page is a summary. For full guidance, use
            <a href="/writing/guides/performance-and-css/">Performance and CSS</a>.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <ul>
            <li>reduce unused CSS</li>
            <li>split CSS by responsibility</li>
            <li>avoid giant global stylesheets</li>
            <li>prefer static-first rendering</li>
            <li>avoid framework CSS overhead where unnecessary</li>
            <li>keep selectors predictable</li>
            <li>contain legacy CSS</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <p>
            Most CSS performance problems in production systems come from scale,
            architecture, and maintainability rather than raw selector speed.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-block">
        <h2>Next useful pages</h2>
        <div class="hub-card-grid">
            <HubCard href="/writing/guides/performance-and-css/" title="Performance and CSS guide">
                <p>Read complete guidance on rendering cost, bundle size, and architecture.</p>
            </HubCard>
            <HubCard href="/writing/guides/performance-and-css/" title="Performance and CSS guide">
                <p>Review architecture trade-offs that influence rendering and delivery cost.</p>
            </HubCard>
            <HubCard href="/apply/architecture/" title="Architecture">
                <p>Use clear structure and ownership to keep CSS performant at scale.</p>
            </HubCard>
        </div>
    </section>
</DocsLayout>
